# CODEOWNERS — auto-assign reviewers on all PRs
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Rows below are grouped by RISK TIER, most-specific-path-wins per GitHub's
# matching rules (a later, more specific pattern overrides an earlier,
# broader one for the paths it covers). All tiers currently resolve to the
# same person (@napetrov is the sole maintainer) — the structure exists so
# that when a second maintainer joins, CRITICAL-tier paths can require a
# narrower, more senior reviewer set without restructuring this file. Don't
# collapse this back to a single `* @napetrov` line; the tiering is the
# point, not the current reviewer list.

# --- Default (fallback for anything not matched below) ---
*                                       @napetrov

# --- CRITICAL: supply-chain / release / security trust boundary ---
# A bad review here can publish a malicious release, exfiltrate secrets, or
# widen what CI is trusted to execute — these paths should get the most
# scrutiny of anything in the repo.
/.github/workflows/publish.yml         @napetrov
/.github/workflows/pages.yml           @napetrov
/.github/workflows/security.yml        @napetrov
/.github/workflows/agentready.yml      @napetrov
/.github/CODEOWNERS                    @napetrov
/action/action.yml                     @napetrov
/action/run.sh                         @napetrov

# --- HIGH: ABI-correctness core (a mistake here is a silent false
# negative/positive in every downstream user's compatibility check) ---
/abicheck/checker_policy.py            @napetrov
/abicheck/checker.py                   @napetrov
/abicheck/diff_symbols.py              @napetrov
/abicheck/diff_types.py                @napetrov
/abicheck/diff_platform.py             @napetrov

# --- STANDARD: everything else CI/workflow-adjacent ---
/.github/                              @napetrov

# --- STANDARD: core library ---
/abicheck/                             @napetrov

# --- STANDARD: tests ---
/tests/                                @napetrov

# --- STANDARD: documentation ---
/docs/                                 @napetrov
*.md                                   @napetrov
/mkdocs.yml                            @napetrov
